  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.",
    "Add the onions and cook until they start to brown, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the garlic and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add the cumin, smoked paprika, salt, and black pepper. Cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add the rest-meat and cook until browned on all sides, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the light rum and cook until the liquid is almost completely evaporated, about 2 minutes.",
    "Transfer the rest-meat mixture to a 9x13-inch baking dish.",
    "Add the mixed bell peppers, chopped dates, and chopped cilantro to the baking dish.",
    "Cover the dish with aluminum foil and bake at 375°F for 30 minutes.",
    "Remove the foil and continue baking for an additional 10-15 minutes, or until the vegetables are tender and the rest-meat is cooked through.",
    "Sprinkle with chopped parsley and serve hot."
  ],
